		%h2 Dear Friend!
		%p
			Welcome to LocalActors.org, a website to create a direct
			link between those who run projects and those who want to support them.
			Few of such websites exist, but none is focusing on local non-for-profit
			projects world-wide while giving a chance to wide range of set-ups.
	.call-container
		%h2 Benefits
		%p
			By sumbmitting your project now you have the benefit of dedicated free help with publishing, longer time to rise money and most of all being seen by all new users when we launch the website in spring! 
			You need only one thing: to have a clear idea about what you want to achieve and how. We will help you to shape the project. We help you to establish what you need for your project to be a success (it might be financing, people help or some materials). We help you to plan your schedule so that is realistic and reliable to your supporters. We also help with writing the right things and ilLustarting them with pictures.
	.call-container		
		%h2 Project Admission
		%p
			In order to publish your project you should think about - results you want to achieve - how to do it - what you need for that - when and what you expect to reach within a month, three month or a year. For a start, try to answer the following questions in an e-mail to weare@localactors.org:
		%ul	
			%li Tell us about yourself and your organisation if you have one.
			%li It would be nice to have a picture of you!
			%li What is your project about and where does it take place?
			%li How do you want to achieve your mission?
			%li Is there anything about the project (pictures, videos, articles) that you would like to share with us?
			
